1
00:00:19,210 --> 00:00:20,830
How's Lucy?

2
00:00:20,980 --> 00:00:22,380
I think she's okay.

3
00:00:22,380 --> 00:00:24,220
She said she wants to take a shower.

4
00:00:24,360 --> 00:00:26,380
So you want me to check on her one more time?

5
00:00:26,380 --> 00:00:29,260
Y-You can't! Not now...

6
00:00:29,260 --> 00:00:30,460
Why not?

7
00:00:32,650 --> 00:00:33,880
Forget it.

8
00:00:34,220 --> 00:00:36,290
The second match is starting.

9
00:00:42,300 --> 00:00:45,250
This kinda thing gets the 
blood pumpin', ya know?

10
00:02:24,490 --> 00:02:26,490
It's the first day of the Grand Magic Games.

11
00:02:26,490 --> 00:02:31,440
The battle part continues 
with the second match,

12
00:02:31,640 --> 00:02:34,950
featuring Ren Akatsuki of Blue Pegasus versus

13
00:02:34,950 --> 00:02:37,920
Arania Webb of Mermaid Heel!

14
00:02:40,980 --> 00:02:42,340
Bad Omen!

15
00:02:44,850 --> 00:02:48,020
It looks like you've improved 
since last year, Arania.

16
00:02:49,420 --> 00:02:54,290
Are you sure it's okay for a member of 
Blue Pegasus to attack a woman, Ren-chan?

17
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:57,510
It seems like both opponents 
are standing their ground!

18
00:02:58,240 --> 00:02:59,740
It should be a good match!

19
00:02:59,740 --> 00:03:02,030
Ren-kun, good luck!

20
00:03:02,030 --> 00:03:05,320
Sherry is cheering you on from the stands!

21
00:03:14,550 --> 00:03:16,650
You're wide open, Ren-chan!

22
00:03:17,410 --> 00:03:19,460
Ren, what are you doing?!

23
00:03:19,460 --> 00:03:21,260
Do your best!

24
00:03:21,880 --> 00:03:24,040
Cut it out, Sherry!

25
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:26,500
You don't root for members of an enemy team!

26
00:03:26,500 --> 00:03:29,940
Oh, come on, Obaba. They <i>are</i> engaged...

27
00:03:29,940 --> 00:03:31,220
Shut up.

28
00:03:31,230 --> 00:03:32,600
Spin.

29
00:03:32,600 --> 00:03:36,150
I'm spinning!

30
00:03:36,730 --> 00:03:39,670
W-Who says we're engaged?!

31
00:03:39,670 --> 00:03:41,790
We just happen to be stuck 
with each other is all!

32
00:03:41,790 --> 00:03:43,380
That's terrible!

33
00:03:44,130 --> 00:03:48,410
It's annoying the way you're 
always by my side...

34
00:03:50,660 --> 00:03:51,630
...but...

35
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:55,040
...when you're not with 
me, I can't get into it.

36
00:03:56,750 --> 00:03:59,190
You're into it!

37
00:03:59,190 --> 00:04:01,170
Oh, Ren...

38
00:04:01,940 --> 00:04:04,850
Sherry sure fell in love 
with a pain in the ass.

39
00:04:05,940 --> 00:04:07,480
But that's love...

40
00:04:07,480 --> 00:04:10,640
The one thing I can't do is look lame

41
00:04:10,900 --> 00:04:12,640
in front of you!

42
00:04:21,070 --> 00:04:23,400
Aerial Phose!

43
00:04:37,710 --> 00:04:39,670
He won!

44
00:04:40,460 --> 00:04:43,940
The winner... Ren Akatsuki of Blue Pegasus!

45
00:04:43,940 --> 00:04:47,370
With this, Blue Pegasus has 
14 points for the first day!

46
00:04:47,370 --> 00:04:49,930
Mermaid Heel has three points!

47
00:04:50,170 --> 00:04:53,480
Shoot... I let down my guard...

48
00:04:54,830 --> 00:04:56,850
That's our Ren-kun!

49
00:04:57,580 --> 00:05:01,020
Unsurprisingly, he's improved 
compared to seven years ago.

50
00:05:01,020 --> 00:05:03,900
Don't tell me that Ichiya's 
gotten stronger, too?!

51
00:05:03,900 --> 00:05:06,700
Natsu, what are you talking about?

52
00:05:06,960 --> 00:05:09,450
Ichiya has always been a man to reckon with.

53
00:05:09,540 --> 00:05:11,130
His personality leaves 
something to be desired,

54
00:05:11,130 --> 00:05:14,120
but there's no denying that he's 
Blue Pegasus's strongest wizard.

55
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:17,080
I didn't know...

56
00:05:17,430 --> 00:05:18,730
Ichiya, huh?

57
00:05:19,670 --> 00:05:22,340
I suddenly wanna fight him!

58
00:05:23,090 --> 00:05:25,340
But what bothers me

59
00:05:25,340 --> 00:05:27,510
is that person in the bunny costume.

60
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:30,810
So it is alright to be bugged by that...

61
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:34,980
Good! I thought maybe we 
weren't supposed to mention it.

62
00:05:40,290 --> 00:05:42,730
Next up, the third match of day one!

63
00:05:42,970 --> 00:05:45,940
War Cry of Quatro Cerberus

64
00:05:46,740 --> 00:05:50,370
versus Orga Nanagear of Team Sabertooth!

65
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:51,920
There he is!

66
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:53,540
It's Orga!

67
00:05:52,750 --> 00:05:54,480
Kick his ass!

68
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:57,520
Listen to those cheers! The crowd loves him!

69
00:05:57,520 --> 00:06:00,210
You can beat him, War Cry!

70
00:06:00,210 --> 00:06:03,550
Your soul is always wild!

71
00:06:06,220 --> 00:06:07,550
It's War Cry.

72
00:06:07,550 --> 00:06:11,320
You gotta see this. I like that guy's magic.

73
00:06:11,320 --> 00:06:13,280
Certainly, it is amusing.

74
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:14,760
I remember it.

75
00:06:15,220 --> 00:06:16,690
Not interested.

76
00:06:30,730 --> 00:06:34,300
I'm only interested... in you...

77
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:35,570
...Gajeel.

78
00:06:36,080 --> 00:06:39,420
We finally get to see a Sabertooth battle.

79
00:06:39,420 --> 00:06:43,590
I wonder if he's as strong 
as that masked ball guy...

80
00:06:44,150 --> 00:06:47,080
Who do you think is gonna win, Lecter?

81
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:49,720
Orga-kun, of course!

82
00:06:50,880 --> 00:06:52,470
Oh, of course...

83
00:06:52,470 --> 00:06:56,540
Sting-kun is number one, but 
everyone in Sabertooth is strong!

84
00:06:56,540 --> 00:07:01,120
You really are dumb, Frosch, 
if you don't even know that.

85
00:07:01,210 --> 00:07:03,480
Fro thinks so, too.

86
00:07:04,050 --> 00:07:07,310
Let the third match begin!

87
00:07:25,500 --> 00:07:28,840
There it is! War Cry's Tear Magic!

88
00:07:28,840 --> 00:07:31,760
That's a funny phrase, isn't it?

89
00:07:32,030 --> 00:07:33,430
He's crying!

90
00:07:33,430 --> 00:07:34,900
Tear Magic?

91
00:07:34,900 --> 00:07:36,650
What kind of magic is that?!

92
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:49,970
The more I cry...

93
00:07:50,700 --> 00:07:55,910
...the stronger I get!

94
00:08:12,410 --> 00:08:13,840
Lightning...

95
00:08:16,190 --> 00:08:18,190
L-Lightning?!

96
00:08:18,190 --> 00:08:20,390
One... attack...

97
00:08:20,650 --> 00:08:23,780
The match is over! Literally, in a flash!

98
00:08:23,780 --> 00:08:27,690
Orga's Black Lightning fried 
the tears instantaneously!

99
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:30,060
What was that?!

100
00:08:30,060 --> 00:08:31,400
Instantaneously?!

101
00:08:31,400 --> 00:08:33,500
H-He's a monster!

102
00:08:33,570 --> 00:08:36,160
He's strong! I mean, really strong!

103
00:08:36,520 --> 00:08:40,440
The winner is Orga Nanagear of Sabertooth!

104
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:42,810
That brings their total to 20 points!

105
00:08:42,810 --> 00:08:45,210
A perfect first day!

106
00:08:45,210 --> 00:08:48,840
Quatro Cerberus has two points! Too bad!

107
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:54,260
Couldn't you have made it more fun, Orga?!

108
00:08:56,980 --> 00:08:58,970
I'll sing a song.

109
00:08:59,230 --> 00:09:01,600
That's not what I meant!

110
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:03,520
Mic!

111
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:10,300
Oh, my! What does Orga Nanagear want to say?!

112
00:09:12,030 --> 00:09:15,820
The strongest, the strongest, number one!

113
00:09:15,820 --> 00:09:19,740
We're the leaders, Sabertooth!

114
00:09:19,740 --> 00:09:23,750
The strongest, the strongest, number one!

115
00:09:23,750 --> 00:09:27,780
We're the leaders, Sabertooth!

116
00:09:27,780 --> 00:09:31,380
The strongest, the strongest, number one!

117
00:09:28,580 --> 00:09:31,380
They really do have raw 
power... and popularity...

118
00:09:31,380 --> 00:09:35,920
We're the leaders, Sabertooth!

119
00:09:31,670 --> 00:09:33,870
They're the strongest guild, huh?

120
00:09:34,310 --> 00:09:37,180
I hate to admit it, but 
those guys are impressive.

121
00:09:38,530 --> 00:09:42,410
Alright, it's time for the 
final match of the first day.

122
00:09:42,410 --> 00:09:47,290
The teams that are left are Fairy 
Tail B and Lamia Scale, right?

123
00:09:47,290 --> 00:09:51,250
Long ago, these two guilds were 
about equal in terms of talent,

124
00:09:51,250 --> 00:09:54,270
so this should be an interesting match!

125
00:09:54,460 --> 00:09:59,020
Okay, I'll announce the first day's 
final fight match-up!

126
00:10:00,850 --> 00:10:04,440
It's Mystogan of Fairy Tail B versus

127
00:10:04,440 --> 00:10:08,580
Jura Neekis of Lamia Scale!

128
00:10:09,830 --> 00:10:11,170
There he is!

129
00:10:11,170 --> 00:10:12,550
Jura!

130
00:10:12,550 --> 00:10:15,250
I've been waiting to see Jura!

131
00:10:15,250 --> 00:10:18,170
I never thought he'd participate 
from the first day!

132
00:10:19,030 --> 00:10:21,180
Jellal all of a sudden?!

133
00:10:21,180 --> 00:10:23,050
And his opponent is Jura!

134
00:10:23,880 --> 00:10:27,650
Even in Fairy Tail, those who 
know his true face are few...

135
00:10:27,650 --> 00:10:29,860
The mysterious wizard, Mystogan!

136
00:10:29,880 --> 00:10:31,470
Who the heck is that?!

137
00:10:31,470 --> 00:10:32,810
That's a laugh!

138
00:10:36,730 --> 00:10:39,190
Good luck, Jura-san!

139
00:10:39,190 --> 00:10:41,010
This match is as good as over.

140
00:10:41,010 --> 00:10:42,970
It hasn't even started yet!

141
00:10:42,970 --> 00:10:45,370
I know that. Stifle yourself.

142
00:10:48,880 --> 00:10:49,870
It's Jura!

143
00:10:49,870 --> 00:10:51,830
Jura's here!

144
00:10:51,830 --> 00:10:53,790
It's the real thing!

145
00:10:54,290 --> 00:10:57,180
That Jura person sure is popular.

146
00:10:57,180 --> 00:11:01,290
Well, sure. He's one of the 
Ten Great Wizard Saints.

147
00:11:01,290 --> 00:11:04,250
The same as our master...

148
00:11:04,440 --> 00:11:06,700
This is unlucky.

149
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:09,270
Going up against Jura...

150
00:11:09,270 --> 00:11:12,560
Is that cueball really that strong?

151
00:11:12,950 --> 00:11:16,650
I don't even know if Erza and I 
could beat him working together...

152
00:11:17,140 --> 00:11:20,340
Leave it to me.

153
00:11:51,300 --> 00:11:55,500
Personally, I'm rooting for Fairy Tail,

154
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:58,230
but our Obaba is really strict about that...

155
00:12:04,670 --> 00:12:07,570
My apologies, but I'm not 
going to hold back here.

156
00:12:08,210 --> 00:12:09,570
Neither am I.

157
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:14,480
This isn't exactly what I'm here for,

158
00:12:15,040 --> 00:12:18,320
but being able to fight 
on behalf of Fairy Tail...

159
00:12:18,870 --> 00:12:20,920
Nothing could make me happier.

160
00:12:30,530 --> 00:12:33,910
No need to worry, First 
Master. It'll be fine.

161
00:12:33,910 --> 00:12:36,990
That man was once a Wizard Saint himself.

162
00:12:36,990 --> 00:12:39,770
In other words, you could 
say their talents are equal.

163
00:12:41,810 --> 00:12:43,290
First Master?

164
00:12:43,290 --> 00:12:46,780
I-I want to go to the ladies' room...

165
00:12:47,160 --> 00:12:49,240
Even though you're a ghost?!

166
00:12:50,060 --> 00:12:53,130
Jellal... Will you be okay?!

167
00:13:03,810 --> 00:13:06,680
Wha...?! Jellal's going to fight?!

168
00:13:06,910 --> 00:13:08,550
His cover won't be blown, will it?

169
00:13:08,740 --> 00:13:11,670
I pray he doesn't make a mess of it...

170
00:13:13,630 --> 00:13:17,690
Mainly, I hope he doesn't 
try to impress Erza.

171
00:13:18,190 --> 00:13:21,550
Jura Neekis of Lamia Scale versus

172
00:13:21,550 --> 00:13:24,070
Mystogan of Fairy Tail B!

173
00:13:24,730 --> 00:13:27,350
Let the final match of the day...

174
00:13:27,520 --> 00:13:29,040
...begin!

175
00:13:29,280 --> 00:13:32,950
What I can do for Fairy Tail...

176
00:13:33,540 --> 00:13:36,660
...is beat you!

177
00:13:50,430 --> 00:13:52,760
Wow!

178
00:14:08,730 --> 00:14:11,290
Five Layered Magic Circle... Sacred Song!

179
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:23,030
So he's copying Mystogan's magic...

180
00:14:23,160 --> 00:14:24,670
Clever...

181
00:14:24,670 --> 00:14:25,910
Jura-san!

182
00:14:25,910 --> 00:14:27,420
There's no need to worry.

183
00:14:28,090 --> 00:14:30,430
With apologies to Juvia's team,

184
00:14:30,550 --> 00:14:35,640
I believe Jura-san is 
Fiore's number one wizard.

185
00:14:35,930 --> 00:14:38,590
Three Layered Magic Circle... Mirror Water!

186
00:14:41,730 --> 00:14:43,380
It ricocheted!

187
00:14:43,380 --> 00:14:44,690
Awesome!

188
00:14:49,110 --> 00:14:50,810
It turned again!

189
00:14:57,260 --> 00:15:01,970
That's some kind of strong! He isn't called 
one of the Ten Great Wizard Saints for nothing!

190
00:15:01,970 --> 00:15:04,940
Now, Jura! Hurry up and finish him off!

191
00:15:04,940 --> 00:15:06,230
Send him spinning!

192
00:15:06,230 --> 00:15:07,630
You're spinning me!

193
00:15:14,290 --> 00:15:18,660
As I suspected, he's not an opponent 
I can beat with borrowed magic.

194
00:15:21,290 --> 00:15:22,560
Meteor!

195
00:15:24,070 --> 00:15:25,150
This guy...

196
00:15:27,820 --> 00:15:29,360
He's fast!

197
00:15:31,740 --> 00:15:33,580
Iron Rock Wall!

198
00:15:49,510 --> 00:15:51,050
There!

199
00:15:54,680 --> 00:15:55,840
I made it!

200
00:16:01,310 --> 00:16:03,320
Magic Circles in the sky!

201
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:04,710
When did he...?!

202
00:16:04,710 --> 00:16:07,530
He must have drawn them while 
defending from the attack.

203
00:16:10,360 --> 00:16:12,530
Be judged by the seven stars!

204
00:16:12,960 --> 00:16:14,380
Grand Chariot!

205
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:24,170
Rock Mountain!

206
00:16:41,910 --> 00:16:43,540
I see...

207
00:16:43,540 --> 00:16:46,560
I know who you are.

208
00:16:46,560 --> 00:16:51,110
So Makarov-dono wasn't being 
entirely candid with me.

209
00:16:51,480 --> 00:16:53,000
Makarov-dono...

210
00:16:53,150 --> 00:16:56,130
A gathering of the Ten Great 
Wizard Saints is coming soon...

211
00:16:56,130 --> 00:17:01,050
...but before then, I'd like you 
to tell me about a certain guild.

212
00:17:01,890 --> 00:17:04,310
I was on guard then,

213
00:17:04,310 --> 00:17:08,750
but I never imagined you would 
pose as a member of Fairy Tail.

214
00:17:09,760 --> 00:17:12,510
My vigilance was for naught.

215
00:17:15,660 --> 00:17:18,870
I have to win for Fairy Tail.

216
00:17:20,450 --> 00:17:22,220
I'm sorry, Ultear.

217
00:17:22,560 --> 00:17:24,410
I'm going to use that!

218
00:17:26,180 --> 00:17:28,630
Wha...?! Jellal!

219
00:17:28,630 --> 00:17:31,950
No! If you use that, your 
cover will be blown!

220
00:17:31,950 --> 00:17:35,460
True Heavenly Body Magic... Cerma!

221
00:17:46,140 --> 00:17:47,830
What is this?!

222
00:17:51,840 --> 00:17:54,380
What the hell is he thinking?!

223
00:17:54,380 --> 00:17:58,420
This is what's wrong with men! Their 
pride gets the better of them!

224
00:17:58,420 --> 00:18:00,090
What should we do, Ul?!

225
00:18:16,470 --> 00:18:17,980
The inside of my mouth...

226
00:18:24,070 --> 00:18:25,520
Spicy!

227
00:18:30,250 --> 00:18:32,620
Eat more red pepper!

228
00:18:32,690 --> 00:18:33,910
Come on, come on...

229
00:18:33,910 --> 00:18:35,630
It's spicy!

230
00:18:41,050 --> 00:18:43,420
What on Earthland is happening?!

231
00:18:43,420 --> 00:18:46,010
Suddenly, Mystogan is in agony!

232
00:18:46,010 --> 00:18:48,020
How about this?!

233
00:18:48,530 --> 00:18:51,560
Stop it, Ul!

234
00:18:59,040 --> 00:19:01,410
And now, he's started laughing!

235
00:19:06,640 --> 00:19:08,480
I've got more...

236
00:19:09,410 --> 00:19:11,460
We can do this...

237
00:19:11,740 --> 00:19:13,640
And this!

238
00:19:14,840 --> 00:19:18,300
I can't take any more! Stop it!

239
00:19:35,810 --> 00:19:37,630
He's down!

240
00:19:39,770 --> 00:19:43,330
I don't really understand 
it, but Mystogan is down!

241
00:19:44,460 --> 00:19:45,910
Sorry about that...

242
00:19:45,910 --> 00:19:49,590
We can't afford to let 
Jellal stand out too much.

243
00:19:52,070 --> 00:19:56,290
The winner is Jura Neekis of Lamia Scale!

244
00:19:58,640 --> 00:20:00,370
You did great, Jura!

245
00:20:01,430 --> 00:20:02,800
Are we sure about this?

246
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:06,410
And with this, the first day of the 
Grand Magic Games comes to a close!

247
00:20:06,410 --> 00:20:09,430
Here's the overall ranking!

248
00:20:11,550 --> 00:20:14,970
A team has zero points and 
B team has one point?!

249
00:20:14,970 --> 00:20:16,740
That's awful...

250
00:20:16,740 --> 00:20:20,500
We shouldn't have participated 
in this thing after all...

251
00:20:26,230 --> 00:20:28,160
What do you think, Yajima-san?

252
00:20:28,290 --> 00:20:30,550
It's no surprise that 
Sabertooth is number one.

253
00:20:30,550 --> 00:20:33,400
On the other hand, Fairy 
Tail, which has two teams,

254
00:20:33,400 --> 00:20:36,000
is in 7th and 8th place.

255
00:20:36,460 --> 00:20:38,850
It's still just the first day.

256
00:20:38,850 --> 00:20:42,590
I'm hoping for a comeback 
drama from tomorrow on.

257
00:20:42,910 --> 00:20:45,390
And my guild still has a shot at victory.

258
00:20:45,390 --> 00:20:47,590
I can't wait for day two!

259
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:51,950
Yajima-san, Jenny-san, thank you 
very much for your commentary today.

260
00:20:51,950 --> 00:20:53,110
Thank <i>you</i>.

261
00:20:53,330 --> 00:20:55,900
See you all again!

262
00:20:58,710 --> 00:21:00,770
What was that?!

263
00:20:59,830 --> 00:21:03,130
What is he, in charge of Fairy Tail's gags?!

264
00:21:03,190 --> 00:21:04,820
That was hilarious!

265
00:21:05,240 --> 00:21:06,790
Ah, well...

266
00:21:06,890 --> 00:21:09,090
What just happened there?!

267
00:21:09,090 --> 00:21:11,130
Meldy's doing, most likely.

268
00:21:12,790 --> 00:21:15,490
What the hell were you doing?!

269
00:21:15,490 --> 00:21:16,860
Good try.

270
00:21:17,230 --> 00:21:18,570
Lame...

271
00:21:19,390 --> 00:21:21,380
I can't even find the words to respond.

272
00:21:24,930 --> 00:21:26,280
Lucy!

273
00:21:27,440 --> 00:21:28,620
Are you alright?

274
00:21:28,620 --> 00:21:30,940
Yeah. I'm fine now.

275
00:21:36,540 --> 00:21:38,500
Last place...

276
00:21:39,420 --> 00:21:41,910
It was the end of the first 
day of the Grand Magic Games.

277
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:46,360
We, Fairy Tail, made a terrible showing...

278
00:21:46,980 --> 00:21:51,480
...but little did we know that even more 
terrible events were already in motion.

279
00:21:53,620 --> 00:21:55,910
She's ripening...

280
00:21:58,610 --> 00:22:01,470
Several days after the end 
of the Grand Magic Games...

281
00:22:01,860 --> 00:22:03,350
...I wrote this down.

282
00:22:03,840 --> 00:22:06,350
This is for you, my dear 
friend, Lucy Heartfilia.

283
00:22:06,670 --> 00:22:08,380
From Levy McGarden.

284
00:22:08,810 --> 00:22:13,250
W-What was that?! A prophecy?!

285
00:22:14,850 --> 00:22:18,770
Don't worry, Lucy! I'll be in it tomorrow!

286
00:22:18,770 --> 00:22:21,730
And I swear I'll turn things around for us!

287
00:23:55,670 --> 00:23:58,460
Natsu, we're in last place! 
We have zero points!

288
00:23:58,460 --> 00:24:00,610
Shut up! We'll turn the tables 
on 'em starting now!

289
00:24:00,610 --> 00:24:02,540
Especially with me participatin' 
in the next competition!

290
00:24:02,810 --> 00:24:05,240
"Chariot", huh? I wonder what 
kind of competition that'll be...

291
00:24:05,240 --> 00:24:07,520
No matter what kind of 
competition, I'm gonna win it!

292
00:24:07,520 --> 00:24:10,470
It looks like that jerk from Saber 
and Gajeel are gonna be in it, too!

293
00:24:10,470 --> 00:24:12,200
That doesn't matter! I'm gonna win!

294
00:24:12,200 --> 00:24:13,930
I'm counting on you, Natsu!

295
00:24:14,110 --> 00:24:16,470
Next time: Chariot!

296
00:24:16,760 --> 00:24:19,970
But "Chariot", that's like a 
vehicle pulled by horses, right?

297
00:24:19,970 --> 00:24:21,140
A vehicle...

298
00:24:21,140 --> 00:24:22,270
I've got a bad feeling about this...

299
00:24:22,270 --> 00:24:24,280
Alright! See ya from the winner's circle!

300
00:24:24,280 --> 00:24:26,740


